comment.author: 39827348@N05
comment._content: Golden Gate operated for a short time after consolidating operations of three commuter airlines: Air Pacific, Oakland, Ca based,  that flew Twin Otters and Dash 7s, Idaho based Gem State Airlines which flew Metroliners and Convair 580s and San Luis Obispo, Ca. based Swift Aire that had a fleet of Fokker F.27.600s and Nord 262s. This company was lead by Justin Colin and after acquiring Charlie Wiswell's Swift Aire their operations as Golden Gate lasted just long enough for them to repaint a few their planes and then the whole company shut down.
